g the limit would be easir to do and can be a part of 3.1 release.\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-01-13T19:01:21.841+0000","updated":"2009-01-13T19:01:21.841+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12412310/comment/12663890","id":"12663890","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"i think the limit should be fixed in 3.1 release and we can open a new jira for getchildren api.... ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-01-14T21:18:31.051+0000","updated":"2009-01-14T21:18:31.051+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12412310/comment/12668364","id":"12668364","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"this patch allows tthe user to set java property jute.maxbuffer at the client. This value is used at the client to throw an error if the read len of value exceeds the set value. By default its set to 4MB.\nif the user wants to cahnge this value, he can do it via setting java property \n-Djute.maxbuffer=someintvalue\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev konar","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2009-01-29T07:27:03.129+0000","updated":"2009-01-29T07:27:03.129+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12412310/comment/12668371","id":"12668371","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nitay","name":"nitay","key":"nitay","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10432","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10432","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10432","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10432"},"displayName":"Nitay Joffe","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"body":"What about having getChildren() return an Iterator<String> instead of a List<String>? Using such an abstraction allows us to put the implementation details of what \"walking the list children\" mean inside ZooKeeper instead of client code. With an Iterator we can make the next() call handle the multiple offset getChildren() calls under the hood, rather than put this burden on the client. Furthermore, if we have, say, some compressed protocol, a lot of space/cpu can be saved by only decompressing/storing the current child being worked on.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=nitay","name":"nitay","key":"nitay","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10432","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10432","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10432","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10432"},"displayName":"Nitay Joffe","active":true,"timeZone":"America/New_York"},"created":"2009-01-29T08:24:53.028+0000","updated":"2009-01-29T08:24:53.028+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12412310/comment/12668373","id":"12668373","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mahadev","name":"mahadev","key":"mahadev","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Mahadev 